Peer dependencies declare what the HOST project must provide. Conflicts happen when two packages need different versions.

```bash
# See the full dependency tree
npm ls react

# Force install (risky — may cause runtime errors)
npm install --legacy-peer-deps

# Better: use overrides to force a specific version
```

```jsonc
// package.json — npm overrides (npm 8.3+)
{
  "overrides": {
    "react": "^18.2.0",
    "some-old-lib": {
      "react": "^18.2.0"  // Override only for this package
    }
